                <h1>Phhttrrrbbh</h1>
                
                
                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
            By <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/monday-monday">Monday Monday</a>
                                    
                                <div class="mt-1">
                                    <span class="can-localize">November 2, 2009 | 5:00am EST</span>
                                </div>
                            </aside>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-left text-md-right d-print-none">
                            <ul class="social-links list-unsyled list-inline mt-4 mt-md-0">
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2009/11/phhttrrrbbh" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2009/11/phhttrrrbbh&amp;text=Phhttrrrbbh" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="twitter" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a></li>
                                                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="mailto:?subject=Phhttrrrbbh%20|%20The%20Chronicle&amp;message=Check%20out%20this%20article%20from%20The%20Chronicle%3A%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dukechronicle.com%2Farticle%2F2009%2F11%2Fphhttrrrbbh" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="email" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fa fa-envelope"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="#" onclick="window.print()" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fas fa-print"></i></a></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                
                <div class="article-content w-100 mb-4">
                                            <p>You know that sound people make when they&rsquo;re holding in a laugh, but they also make it when they&rsquo;re mocking something? The one where it&rsquo;s this nasal-guttural sound that&rsquo;s technically the beginning of a chuckle but sounds dangerously close to a snorting sound. &nbsp;</p>
<p>Yeah, that sound is really hard to transliterate. I&rsquo;ve experimented for a while, and I decided that &ldquo;Phhttrrrbbh&rdquo; is the closest you&rsquo;re gonna get.</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
            <div id="azk18664"></div>
    <!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
                        </div>

                        <p>For instance: If I were to say, &ldquo;Hey, I&rsquo;m concerned the Young Trustee open forums are going to be overflowing, do you think we should tell them to move them to someplace bigger?&rdquo; you would be correct to respond, &ldquo;Phhttrrrbbh!&rdquo;</p>
<p>With all the options open for Duke students this Halloweekend, there were a lot of opportunities to dismissively &ldquo;Phhttrrrbbh&rdquo; things.</p>
<p>Among the &ldquo;Phhttrrrbbh-able&rdquo;:</p>
<p>Watching the World Series. Who watches baseball anymore, really? Thirty years ago, when the Pittsburgh (where?) Pirates beat the Baltimore Orioles (what-now?), almost 38 million people watched it. Adjusted for inflation, that&rsquo;s like a billion people. Today, a game between the Pirates and Orioles would draw about six viewers, likely single obese men aged 35 to 50 who haven&rsquo;t showered in the previous month before the game. Last year&rsquo;s World Series (a real doozy, if you ask me) drew less than 14 million. &nbsp;</p>
<p>This year, it&rsquo;s a competition between the team most hated around the nation (the Yankees) and the team most hated in their own town (the Phillies). Major League Baseball could not have orchestrated a more loathsome World Series.</p>
<p>In fact, although I moan and groan about the decline of baseball, I didn&rsquo;t even watch the World Series. I spent my Halloween chilling at Devil&rsquo;s Eve staring at guys&rsquo; crotches as they walked by. Normally, that sort of attention is welcome, but when a few approached me to talk about where we go from here, I explained to them that it was part of my costume. I was Alex Rodriguez, reverted to his normal choke-artist form just in time for the October Classic, just watching balls go by. I guess these conversations sort of improved the look, as it inevitably led to me striking out with men aboard.</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
        <div id="azk5125"></div>
<!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
                        </div>

                                                                            <p>Speaking of which, Devil&rsquo;s Eve was pretty &ldquo;Phhttrrrbbh-able.&rdquo; After Chapel Hill decided to again restrict access to one of the best Halloween parties in the country, Campus Council swooped in and filled the void&mdash;and then some! Not only was there a costume contest, there was also a live performance of the Thriller dance! Like, omg, wow!</p>
<p>Phhttrrrbbh.</p>
<p>Okay, so maybe you weren&rsquo;t watching the World Series or lame-ing the night away at Devil&rsquo;s Eve. You could have gone to see the Duke Players Lab performance of &ldquo;Nevermore&rdquo;&hellip;. Phhttrrrbbh.</p>
<p>It&rsquo;s true, there&rsquo;s nothing that says Halloween like a death-metal infused re-interpretation of the Gothic Wonder-boy in the Gothic Wonderland (translation: Edgar Allen Poe at Duke University). And a raven that crows at you as you walk by it on the Plaza all week does kinda set the mood for a Halloween experience so sombre and grotesque that you can only spell s-o-m-b-r-e the British way.</p>
                            
    
<div class="mc-signup my-4 p-4 text-center " id="mc-container" data-mc="c4087a59c7">
    <h3>Get The Chronicle straight to your inbox</h3>
    <p>Signup for our editorially curated, weekly newsletter. Cancel at any time.</p>
